</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup and phrase 1 (m.0-5): Sparse LH (3 notes), gentle 2-note RH. Em modal center.
  vii° (F#°) in m.5 voiced as F#2 A2 C3 — diminished triad, distinctive color.
- Phrase 2 (m.6-9): Same modal material but D "33" full triad + dotted-half sustain
  gives breathing room; m.6 RH opens to C5 E5 (Am 1st inv) — more expansive.
- Refrain phrase 3 (m.10-13): D→Bm→G brighter harmonies; climax at m.12 with G Δ7
  in LH (G2 B2 D3 F#3), RH reaches B4 D5 G5 — full 3-note high register.
- Refrain phrase 4 (m.14-19): Similar to phrase 3 but RH moves into even higher register
  (D5 F#5 for Bm); final Em in m.19 with 3-note RH chord (G4 B4 E5).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH descending line C5→A4→G4→F#4 in mm.5 and 18 — inner voice countermelody.
- m.2 / m.11 / m.15: D7 voiced as D2 A2 C3 F#3 (7th in LH explicitly) creates resolution
  pull to Em that follows.
- m.12 climax: G Δ7 LH + G5 top RH note — widest range of the arrangement.
- m.13: D "34" 2nd-inversion (A4 in bass) gives unstable cadential 6/4 feel before Em.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening (pickup, m.1-5): Sparse, 3-note LH, 2-note RH, narrow range. Modal/mystical.
- Middle phrases (m.6-9): Sustained half-note LH adds weight; breathing room.
- Refrain (m.10-13): Shorter note values, brighter D/G harmonies; climax m.12.
- Final refrain (m.14-19): Slightly denser LH; RH at highest range; resolution to Em.
-->
